The paper deals with the spatial degrees of freedom of MIMO channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on multicell and multiuser scenarios, which are relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and communication engineering (cs.CE). The paper also explores linear schemes and interference alignment, which are common techniques in signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia systems (cs.MM).
